{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]Beautiful dreamer queen of my [C]song
[Am]List while I woo thee [D7]with soft [G7]melody
[C]Gone are the cares of life's busy [Dm]throng
[G7]Beautiful dreamer awake unto [C]me
[F]Beautiful [C]dreamer [G7]awake unto [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[Dm]Beautiful Dreamer out on the sea
[G7]Mermaids are chanting the wild [C]Lorelei
[Dm]Over the streamlet vapors are borne
[G7]Waiting to fade at the bright coming [C]morn
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[G7]Beautiful Dreamer beam on my [C]heart
[Am]Even as the morn on the [D7]streamlet and [G7]sea
[C]Then will all clouds of sorrow [Dm]depart
[G7]Beautiful Dreamer awake unto [C]me
[F]Beautiful [C]Dreamer [G7]awake unto [C]me
{end_of_verse}
